      "writtenOn": "2019-01-05T02:38:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please either use luci-go\u0027s logging module (preferred) or just plain old fmt.Printf. Other parts of luci-go (linked from this code) use luci-go\u0027s logging. Mixing different logging systems is bad.\n\nSo something like:\n\nlogging.Logf(ctx, lvl, \"%s: %s\", message.Path, message.Text)\n\nwhere \u0027lvl\u0027 is either logging.Warning or logging.Error based on message.Severity.\n\n\u0027logging\u0027 is http://go.chromium.org/luci/common/logging",
      "range": {
